01:04:11.000 --> 01:04:21.000
Madga Evers was the executive director of the NAACP. He was a person who went disguised to get information about the Emmett Till case.

01:04:21.000 --> 01:04:35.000
He was the political leader of the NAACP in Mississippi. He was very involved in a lot of political activity and civil rights involvement in the state.

01:04:35.000 --> 01:04:36.000
And Tom Gather?

01:04:36.000 --> 01:04:46.000
Tom Gather was a core member early in Mississippi and continues to be involved in the civil rights movement to the state.

01:04:46.000 --> 01:04:52.000
Now you mentioned when you were talking about the Freedom House address earlier that it was a place of reconciliation. What did you mean by that?

01:04:52.000 --> 01:04:58.000
